added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a young girl learn unconventional survival skills that help rescue her endangered camping troop.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Retires
added.description: Uncle Grandpa discovers a new, unusual occupation.

added.title: Funny Face
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa accidentally unleashes a floating Funny Face that's so funny you laugh yourself to insanity, the guys realize that only Gus' seriousness can save them, but will he help them after they've hurt his feelings?

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Sitter
added.description: Gus and Pizza Steve have plans to go out for the night, but UG can't be left alone in the RV, so they need a babysitter.  But when none are available, they turn to UG to babysit himself.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa for a Day
added.description: When UG gets his head stuck in a peanut butter jar, Mr. Gus and Pizza Steve have to pretend to be UG and help a kid.

added.title: Treasure Map
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang don't have money to pay for their meal at a restaurant.  But when they discover a treasure map, it could be the answer to all their problems.  Too bad the treasure map is actually a restaurant activity placemat.

added.title: Vacation
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes on vacation only to discover that being Uncle Grandpa is a full time job.

added.title: Uncle Caveman
added.description: In this prehistoric-themed episode, Uncle Grandpa must save his new friend, Mr. Gus, from a hoard of hungry cavemen.

removed.title: Saving Private Masko
removed.description: Masko takes Axel's call for more discipline too seriously and loses sight of his own identity in the process, becoming a no-nonsense soldier set on toeing the line - and ill-equipped for a lucha libre with Madcap!

removed.title: Mumm-Ra, el Inmortal
removed.description: Cada vez que Mumm-Ra se hace con un artefacto mágico para restablecer sus poderes, los ThunderCats lo destrozan y vuelven a convertirlo en un esqueleto. Hasta hoy, porque Mumm-Ra acaba de recordar que cuenta con los Antiguos Espíritus del Mal, y ahora, podrá ponerse fuerte siempre que quiera.

removed.title: Bearz II Men
removed.description: The Baby Bears help a teenager accomplish his dream of being a famous singer.

removed.title: El Comienzo de Cobrangutan
removed.description: Mao Mao incita a Cobrangután y a los Piratas del Cielo a convertirse en villanos verdaderamente malvados, dignos de un héroe legendario como él.

removed.title: Time Share
removed.description: Batman and Blue Beetle have to travel back in time to stop Chronos from destroying a young Dark Knight on his very first case.

removed.title: It Grows
removed.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

removed.title: Saving Faith
removed.description: Lloyd and his team plot to take control of the Oni Titan. Meanwhile in the First Realm, the Ninja fall into Iron Baron's clutches and an old master returns.

removed.title: Zombie King
removed.description: Grundy escapes his Louisiana prison intent on using a magical crystal which will allow him to raise the dead from their graves. Only Batman and Swamp thing stand in the way of his growing zombie army.

removed.title: Earthlings
removed.description: Amethyst tries to exact revenge with a showdown in the Kindergarten.

removed.title: While You Were Away
removed.description: Dr. Psychobos and Princess Attea have invaded Rook's home planet Revonnah with an army of Incurseans! (Introducing new Ben alien, Astrodactyl.)

removed.title: Need for Speed
removed.description: Touring Yellowstone, Ben uncovers a plot by the fast & furious LaGrange to find treasure buried below the national park, but with a little help from Old Faithful, Overflow is able to douse LaGrange's dreams.

removed.title: El eslabon mas debil
removed.description: Lloyd le paga con la misma moneda a Harumi para quitarle el poder a su padre, y los Ninjas aprenden lo que se necesita para ser un Cazador de Dragones.
removed.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

removed.title: Porque tan triste?
removed.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

removed.title: Omni-Tricked
removed.description: Ben's vacation to Portland is cut short when he discovers an 11th alien while battling a Dr. Animo Mega-Creature. But when the fight leaves his Omnitrix on the fritz cycling through all 11 aliens, Max seeks help from an old friend to fix the Omnitrix as other dangerous forces seek it including a mysterious alien that's the same species as the 11th alien, Vilgax!

removed.title: La Fe
removed.description: Alan perdió su fe en la humanidad y puso el mundo blanco y negro. Gumball tiene que superar el odio que siente hacia Alan para recuperar el color a través del canto.
removed.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

removed.title: Omni-Truco
removed.description: Ben debe interrumpir sus vacaciones en Portland cuando descubre un 11mo alien al luchar contra la mega criatura del Dr. Animal. Pero, como la lucha deja a su Omnitrix todo estropeado pasando por los 11 aliens, Max pide ayuda a un viejo amigo para que repare el Omnitrix, que es perseguido por otras fuerzas peligrosas, entre ellas un alien misterioso de la misma especie que el 11mo alien...iVilgax!

removed.title: Head Chef
removed.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

removed.title: Cruisin
removed.description: Mordecai and Rigby make a bet with Margaret and Eileen that they can get a girl's phone number by cruising.

removed.title: Crece
removed.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

removed.title: Squirreled Domination
removed.description: Rare food enthusiast Fud sends the Warriors on a mission to the Deepest Darkest Woods to gather five golden acorns from a golden oak tree for a golden acorn casserole, but poor Vambre has a secret fear of squirrels, and it turns out that golden squirrels are the scariest of them all!

removed.title: Debiste estar ahi
removed.description: Los Titanes viajan en el tiempo hacia sus aventuras pasadas e insertan a Bumblebee en sus memorias para que ella no se sienta excluida de sus chistes internos.

removed.title: Un Episodio Muy Especial
removed.description: Cuarzo Arcoíris 2.0 prometió cuidar de Cebolla el mismo día que Heliolita programó una charla sobre la seguridad del hogar. ¿Es posible para Steven estar en dos lugares a la vez y ser dos fusiones al mismo tiempo?

removed.title: Se busca Brock
removed.description: Cuando Master Frown comienza a arruinar fiestas para ganar un ascenso de sus jefes, los Señores de la Muerte, Brock accidentalmente es culpado por las desgracias.

removed.title: Career Day
removed.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

removed.title: Vreedlemania
removed.description: Pa Vreedle reunites with Ma for all-out destruction.

removed.title: Worm Bin
removed.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

removed.title: Bad Timing

But when Mom and Dad say they're going to spend the money on paying bills instead, it's a race to the bank to see who can cash the check first.
